(40, 24, 30, 38, 12, 10, 10, NULL, 'Mourning for the Pierced One', 'Both passages emphasize mourning related to the Son of man. Matthew speaks of tribes mourning upon seeing Him, while Zechariah describes mourning for the one who was pierced.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 31, 52, 4, 16, 16, 'gather together his elect', 'Connection of Gathering and Trumpet', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of believers and the use of a trumpet. Matthew 24:31 mentions angels gathering the elect, while 1 Thessalonians 4:16 describes the Lord''s descent with the trump of God.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 31, 41, 13, 27, 27, 'gather together his elect from the four winds', 'Gathering of the Elect', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of the elect by angels. They share similar phrases about gathering from the four winds, indicating a thematic connection.', 'parallel', 0.482, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 31, 23, 27, 13, 13, NULL, 'Gathering of the Elect', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of people through the blowing of a trumpet. Matthew speaks of angels gathering the elect, while Isaiah describes people coming from Assyria and Egypt to worship.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 31, 46, 15, 52, 52, NULL, 'Connection of the Last Trumpet', 'Both passages emphasize the sounding of a trumpet as a pivotal moment for gathering the elect and raising the dead. This connection highlights the theme of divine intervention at the end times.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 31, 23, 11, 12, 12, 'gather together', 'Gathering of the Elect', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of people from various locations, highlighting a divine assembly. The phrase ''gather together'' in Matthew parallels the assembly of the dispersed in Isaiah.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 31, 40, 13, 41, 41, 'gather together his elect', 'Gathering by Angels', 'Both passages emphasize the role of angels in gathering. Matthew 24:31 speaks of angels gathering the elect, while Matthew 13:41 describes angels gathering those who offend. This connection highlights the function of angels in divine judgment and gathering.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 31, 53, 2, 1, 1, 'gather together his elect', 'Gathering of the Elect', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of believers. Matthew speaks of angels gathering the elect, while 2 Thessalonians refers to the gathering together unto Christ.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 32, 41, 13, 28, 29, 'learn a parable of the fig tree', 'Fig Tree Parable Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the fig tree as a sign of approaching summer, illustrating a theme of recognizing signs of change. The similar phrasing in both verses indicates a shared teaching on awareness of impending events.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 32, 42, 21, 29, 30, 'fig tree', 'Fig Tree Parable Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the fig tree as a sign of the approaching season. They illustrate the idea that observing the fig tree''s growth indicates that summer is near.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 33, 59, 5, 9, 9, NULL, 'Judgment and Awareness', 'Both passages emphasize the imminent presence of judgment. Matthew speaks of recognizing signs that indicate the end is near, while James warns against grievances, noting that ''the judge standeth before the door.''', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 33, 58, 10, 37, 37, 'even at the doors', 'Expectation of Christ''s Return', 'Both passages emphasize the imminent return of Christ. Matthew 24:33 indicates that His coming is ''even at the doors,'' while Hebrews 10:37 assures that He ''will come, and will not tarry.''', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 33, 26, 7, 2, 14, 'it is near, even at the doors', 'Judgment and the End Times', 'Both passages emphasize the imminent arrival of judgment and the end. Matthew 24:33 speaks of recognizing signs that indicate the end is near, while Ezekiel 7:2-14 declares that ''the end is come'' and describes impending judgment. This connection highlights a thematic parallel regarding divine retribution.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 33, 60, 4, 7, 7, 'it is near, even at the doors', 'End Times Awareness', 'Both passages emphasize the nearness of the end. Matthew 24:33 states that it is ''even at the doors,'' while 1 Peter 4:7 declares that ''the end of all things is at hand.'' This connection highlights a call to vigilance and prayer in light of impending events.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 33, 66, 3, 20, 20, 'even at the doors', 'Connection of Doors and Presence', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being near or at the door, suggesting an imminent presence. Matthew speaks of recognizing signs that indicate something is near, while Revelation invites individuals to open the door for Christ''s presence.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 34, 41, 13, 30, 31, 'this generation shall not pass', 'Connection of Generational Fulfillment', 'Both passages emphasize that ''this generation shall not pass'' until certain events are fulfilled. This highlights a shared theme of the urgency and certainty of prophetic fulfillment.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 34, 40, 16, 28, 28, 'This generation shall not pass', 'Connection of Generational Fulfillment', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a generation witnessing significant events. Matthew 24:34 speaks of a generation not passing until fulfillment occurs, while Matthew 16:28 indicates some will see the Son of man coming in his kingdom.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 34, 42, 21, 32, 33, 'This generation shall not pass', 'Connection of Generational Fulfillment', 'Both passages emphasize that ''this generation shall not pass away'' until all is fulfilled, indicating a shared theme of prophetic fulfillment within a specific timeframe. Additionally, the mention of the permanence of Jesus'' words in Luke reinforces the certainty of the prophecy''s fulfillment.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 34, 40, 23, 36, 36, 'this generation', 'Connection of Generational Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''this generation'' facing impending fulfillment of prophetic events. The use of ''this generation'' in both contexts highlights a specific audience that will witness these occurrences.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 34, 42, 11, 50, 50, 'this generation', 'Connection of Generational Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize ''this generation'' in relation to judgment. Matthew speaks of fulfillment of events within this generation, while Luke refers to the accountability of this generation for the blood of the prophets.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 35, 4, 23, 19, 19, 'my words shall not pass away', 'Enduring Nature of God''s Word', 'Both passages emphasize the reliability of God''s words. Matthew asserts that His words shall not pass away, while Numbers affirms that God will fulfill what He has spoken.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 35, 19, 89, 34, 34, 'my words shall not pass away', 'Enduring Nature of God''s Words', 'Both passages emphasize the permanence of God''s words. Matthew highlights that His words will not pass away, while Psalms asserts that His covenant will not be altered.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 35, 19, 102, 26, 26, 'my words shall not pass away', 'Endurance of God''s Word', 'Both passages emphasize the enduring nature of God''s words and existence. While heaven and earth will pass away, God''s words remain, paralleling the idea that all created things will perish, but God endures forever.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 35, 20, 30, 5, 5, 'my words shall not pass away', 'Enduring Nature of God''s Words', 'This connection highlights the enduring quality of God''s words. Both passages emphasize that God''s words are unchanging and trustworthy, providing protection to those who believe.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 35, 23, 40, 8, 8, 'my words shall not pass away', 'Enduring Nature of God''s Word', 'Both passages emphasize that the word of God shall stand forever, contrasting it with the transient nature of the physical world. This connection highlights the permanence of divine communication amidst temporal change.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 35, 23, 51, 6, 6, NULL, 'Eternal Nature of God''s Words', 'Both passages emphasize the transient nature of heaven and earth while affirming the permanence of God''s words and salvation. This connection highlights the contrast between the temporal world and the eternal truth of God''s promises.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 35, 40, 5, 18, 18, 'heaven and earth shall pass away', 'Endurance of God''s Word', 'Both passages emphasize the permanence of God''s words and laws despite the passing of heaven and earth. They highlight the enduring nature of divine revelation and its fulfillment.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 36, 41, 13, 32, 32, 'knoweth no man, no, not the angels', 'Connection of Knowledge of Time', 'Both passages emphasize that no one knows the specific day or hour except the Father. This shared theme highlights the mystery surrounding the timing of future events.', 'theme', 0.685, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 36, 44, 1, 7, 7, NULL, 'Knowledge of Times and Seasons', 'Both passages emphasize that knowledge of specific times is reserved for the Father alone. This connection highlights the limitation of human understanding regarding divine timing.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 24, 36, 40, 24, 44, 44, NULL, 'Readiness for the Unknown', 'Both passages emphasize the uncertainty of the timing of the Son of man's coming. The first verse states that no one knows the day or hour, while the second urges readiness for an unexpected arrival.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
